{"format": "tiptap/v1", "updatedAt": "2026-06-21T17:40:28.688Z", "doc": {"type": "doc", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Expectation"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (also called expected value or mean) and "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Variance"}, {"type": "text", "text": " are the two fundamental measures that describe the behavior of random variables: expectation tells you the "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "average outcome"}, {"type": "text", "text": " you'd see over many trials (the \"center\" of the distribution), while variance quantifies how much outcomes "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "spread out"}, {"type": "text", "text": " from that average (the \"uncertainty\" or \"dispersion\"). Together, they form the backbone of probability theory and are essential for understanding data distributions, model uncertainty, and optimization in machine learning."}]}, {"type": "image", "attrs": {"src": "data:image/svg+xml;base64,", "alt": "Expectation & Variance — concept overview"}}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "What it is — Clear definition and intuition"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Expectation (Expected Value):"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Definition"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": The average value you would expect if you repeat an experiment many times."}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Conceptual meaning"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": The \"center of mass\" of a probability distribution."}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Formula for discrete random variables"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "text"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "E[X] = Σ x · P(X = x)"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Formula for continuous random variables"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "text"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "E[X] = ∫ x · f(x) dx"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "In simple words"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Sum (or integrate) all possible values weighted by their probability."}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Analogy"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": If you play a game 1,000 times, E is the average score you'd get."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Variance:"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Definition"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Measures how much a random variable deviates from its mean (average)."}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Conceptual meaning"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Average "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "squared distance"}, {"type": "text", "text": " from the mean."}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Formula"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "text"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Var(X) = E[(X - E[X])²]"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "In simple words"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": How spread out the values are around the mean."}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Alternative (equivalent) formula"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "text"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Var(X) = E[X²] - (E[X])²"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Why squared?"}, {"type": "text", "text": " Squaring ensures positive values and emphasizes large deviations."}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Analogy"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Two classes have the same average score (80), but Class A has scores 79-81 (low variance), while Class B has scores 60-100 (high variance)."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Key distinction:"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Measure"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "What it tells you"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Symbol"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Expectation"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Center/average (location)"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "E or μ"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Variance"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Spread/uncertainty (dispersion)"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Var(X) or σ²"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "[linkedin](https://www.linkedin.com/posts/man-with-machine-learning_expectation-variance-covariance-correlation-activity-7371745155269402624-u4Jx)"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Why it matters — Importance in Generative AI"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Expectation and variance are critical for ML systems:"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "ML Application"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "How expectation/variance apply"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Loss Minimization"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Train model to minimize E (average error)"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Uncertainty Quantification"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "High variance = uncertain predictions"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Model Evaluation"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Compare models using mean accuracy (E) and variance"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Regularization"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Variance regularization prevents overfitting"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Generative Models"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "VAEs model data as distributions with mean & variance"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Feature Selection"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Covariance matrix (built from variance) guides PCA"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Optimization"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Gradient descent minimizes expected loss"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Real example"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": In a GPT model, the expected loss tells you average prediction error; variance tells you how consistent predictions are across different inputs."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "How to compute — Step-by-step examples"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Example 1: Discrete random variable (fair die)"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "yaml"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "X = outcome of rolling a fair 6-sided die\nP(X = 1) = P(X = 2) = ... = P(X = 6) = 1/6\n\nExpectation:\nE[X] = Σ x · P(X = x)\n     = 1×(1/6) + 2×(1/6) + 3×(1/6) + 4×(1/6) + 5×(1/6) + 6×(1/6)\n     = (1 + 2 + 3 + 4 + 5 + 6) / 6\n     = 21 / 6\n     = 3.5\n\nVariance:\nVar(X) = E[(X - 3.5)²]\n       = (1-3.5)²×(1/6) + (2-3.5)²×(1/6) + ... + (6-3.5)²×(1/6)\n       = 6.25/6 + 2.25/6 + 0.25/6 + 0.25/6 + 2.25/6 + 6.25/6\n       = 29.5 / 6\n       ≈ 4.92\n\nStandard deviation: σ = √Var(X) ≈ √4.92 ≈ 2.22"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Alternative variance calculation"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "text"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Var(X) = E[X²] - (E[X])²\n\nE[X²] = 1²×(1/6) + 2²×(1/6) + ... + 6²×(1/6)\n      = (1 + 4 + 9 + 16 + 25 + 36) / 6\n      = 91 / 6\n      ≈ 15.17\n\nVar(X) = 15.17 - (3.5)²\n       = 15.17 - 12.25\n       = 2.92  ✓ (matches)"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Example 2: Continuous random variable (normal distribution)"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "yaml"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "X ~ Normal(μ=0, σ=1)  # Standard normal\n\nProperties:\nE[X] = μ = 0\nVar(X) = σ² = 1"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "By definition"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Normal distribution is parameterized by expectation (μ) and variance (σ²)."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Example 3: Bernoulli random variable (coin flip)"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "yaml"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "X = 1 if heads, X = 0 if tails\nP(X = 1) = p (e.g., p = 0.5 for fair coin)\nP(X = 0) = 1 - p\n\nExpectation:\nE[X] = 1×p + 0×(1-p)\n     = p\n\nVariance:\nVar(X) = E[X²] - (E[X])²\n       = (1²×p + 0²×(1-p)) - p²\n       = p - p²\n       = p(1 - p)\n\nFor fair coin (p = 0.5):\nE[X] = 0.5\nVar(X) = 0.5 × 0.5 = 0.25"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Key properties — Mathematical rules"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Expectation properties:"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Property"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Formula"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Linearity"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "E[aX + b] = a·E + b"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Sum of RVs"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "E[X + Y] = E + E[Y]"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Constant"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "E[c] = c (expectation of constant is itself)"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Product"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "E[X·Y] = E·E[Y] "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "if X, Y independent"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Linearity example"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "text"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "E[2X + 3] = 2·E[X] + 3"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Variance properties:"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Property"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Formula"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Constant"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Var(c) = 0 (constant has no spread)"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Scaling"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Var(aX) = a²·Var(X)"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Sum (independent)"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Var(X + Y) = Var(X) + Var(Y) "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "if X, Y independent"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Sum (general)"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Var(X + Y) = Var(X) + Var(Y) + 2·Cov(X,Y)"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Scaling example"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "text"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Var(2X) = 2²·Var(X) = 4·Var(X)"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Why a²?"}, {"type": "text", "text": " Variance measures squared deviations, so scaling factor squares."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Relationship to standard deviation:"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "text"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Standard Deviation: σ = √Var(X)"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Why use it?"}, {"type": "text", "text": " Standard deviation has same units as X (not squared), making it more interpretable."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Python implementation"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Computing expectation and variance:"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "import numpy as np\n\n# Simulate rolling a fair die 10,000 times\nrolls = np.random.randint(1, 7, size=10000)\n\n# Expectation (sample mean)\nexpectation = np.mean(rolls)\nprint(f\"Expected value (E[X]): {expectation:.3f}\")  # ≈ 3.5\n\n# Variance\nvariance = np.var(rolls, ddof=1)  # ddof=1 for sample variance\nprint(f\"Variance (Var(X)): {variance:.3f}\")  # ≈ 2.92\n\n# Standard deviation\nstd_dev = np.std(rolls, ddof=1)\nprint(f\"Standard Deviation: {std_dev:.3f}\")  # ≈ 1.71"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Verifying formulas:"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "import numpy as np\n\n# Bernoulli: coin flip with p = 0.5\np = 0.5\ncoin_flips = np.random.binomial(n=1, p=p, size=10000)\n\n# Analytical formulas\nE_X_analytical = p\nVar_X_analytical = p * (1 - p)\n\n# Empirical formulas\nE_X_empirical = np.mean(coin_flips)\nVar_X_empirical = np.var(coin_flips, ddof=1)\n\nprint(f\"Analytical: E[X] = {E_X_analytical}, Var(X) = {Var_X_analytical}\")\nprint(f\"Empirical: E[X] = {E_X_empirical:.3f}, Var(X) = {Var_X_empirical:.3f}\")"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "For continuous distributions:"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "import numpy as np\nfrom scipy import stats\n\n# Generate samples from normal distribution\nsamples = np.random.normal(loc=5, scale=2, size=10000)  # μ=5, σ=2\n\n# Expectation and variance\nexpectation = np.mean(samples)\nvariance = np.var(samples, ddof=1)\n\nprint(f\"E[X] = {expectation:.3f} (analytical: 5)\")\nprint(f\"Var(X) = {variance:.3f} (analytical: 4)\")"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Common mistakes — Pitfalls to avoid"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Mistake"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Correction"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Confusing variance with standard deviation"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Variance = σ² (squared units); Std Dev = σ (same units)"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Using Var(X + Y) = Var(X) + Var(Y) blindly"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Only works if X, Y are independent"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Forgetting E[X + Y] = E + E[Y] always holds"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Linearity of expectation is always true, even for dependent variables"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Computing sample variance incorrectly"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Use "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "np.var(ddof=1)"}, {"type": "text", "text": " for sample variance (unbiased)"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Key takeaways"}]}, {"type": "orderedList", "attrs": {"start": 1, "type": null}, "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Expectation = average outcome"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": E = Σ x·P(X=x) for discrete; E = ∫ x·f(x)dx for continuous"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Variance = spread around mean"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Var(X) = E[(X - E)²] = E[X²] - (E)²"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Expectation measures location"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Tells you where the \"center\" of the distribution is"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Variance measures uncertainty"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": High variance = scattered outcomes; Low variance = clustered"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Linearity of expectation"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": E[X + Y] = E + E[Y] always true"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Variance scaling"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Var(aX) = a²·Var(X) (scales quadratically)"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Independence"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Var(X + Y) = Var(X) + Var(Y) only if X, Y independent"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Standard deviation"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": σ = √Var(X) (more interpretable than variance)"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Loss minimization"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": ML trains to minimize E (expected error)"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Uncertainty quantification"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Variance tells you how confident predictions are"}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "For Generative AI, expectation and variance are fundamental: they quantify model uncertainty (variance in predictions), guide optimization (minimize expected loss), and enable probabilistic modeling (distributions parameterized by mean and variance)."}]}]}}